IDE is a cytosolic enzyme that degrades misfolded proteins, while MICB is a chaperone that promotes proper folding of MHC class II molecules. ERAP1 and ERAP2 are involved in the processing and trimming of MHC class II-bound peptides. HLA-E is a non-classical MHC class II molecule that presents peptides to T cells. ULBP1, HFE, and ULBP3 are ligands for activating NKG2D receptors on NK cells and some T cells.
